About this hotel

Set in the city's medieval walled medina, this elegant guesthouse comprises several interconnected buildings. It's a 5-minute walk from the bustling, iconic Jemaa el-Fnaa square and 6 km from Marrakesh Menara Airport.

Check-in time: 2:00 PM
Check-out time: 11:00 AM

    Medina

    Hammam bath houses and covered spice and textile souks line the maze of cobblestoned lanes in the Medina, which occupies Marrakeshs original fortified citadel. At night, Jemaa el-Fna square teems with snake charmers, folk dancers, and street food vendors serving all manner of food. Bahia Palace and Le Jardin Secret are 19th-century complexes open to the public, with ornate courtyards, mosaics, and gardens.

    About this hotel

    Set in the city's medieval walled medina, this elegant guesthouse comprises several interconnected buildings. It's a 5-minute walk from the bustling, iconic Jemaa el-Fnaa square and 6 km from Marrakesh Menara Airport.

    Cozy rooms offer Wi-Fi, flat-screen TVs, safes, and minifridges, plus en suite or private bathrooms. Some rooms feature distinct touches such as hand-painted murals, carved wood furnishings, Ionic-inspired columns and/or chandeliers. A polished suite adds a sofa.

    A spa has a hammam, an indoor pool and a hot tub. There's also a refined dining room and a quaint courtyard, as well as terraces. A breakfast buffet is available.
